snippet.textDisplay:
In May 2019, members of the Minnesota House of Representatives and the Minnesota Senate sent official letters to the Minnesota Medical Association (MMA) expressing concern over forced organ harvesting in China.

The letters from the House of Representatives and the Minnesota Senate, written by Representative Nels Pierson (R-Stewartville) and Senator Jim Abeler (R-Anoka), were supported by 77 House and Senate co-signers, two of whom are practicing physicians. Both letters expressed concern over Minnesota residents obtaining unethically sourced organs from countries such as China and also mentioned concern over, “…Chinese medical personnel who are trained in Minnesota that may assist in forced organ harvesting.”

snippet.textDisplay:
Please try to buy more sustainable foods! You can make your own coleslaw for example, with very few ingredients and it's also fun to make! Once you get all the spices and herbs you need you can live on loose fresh fruit veg and grains and you won't need to buy any products that come in packaging! Store loose pasta, cereals, teabags, left overs in jars and sustainable lunch boxes and use labels to put the name of product and use by date! Jars on shelves look super cute as well as reducing waste! Also this way you tend to use less from the jars and your items last longer, until you refill them at a Refill Store, which is like pick and mix machines but for pasta rice beans sugar coffee that you fill using your own jars etc, and any liquids like sauces and cleaning products and (plant) milk to fill your own bottles with! Making a waste free kitchen starting with the kitchen is an amazing thing to do and I recommend xxxxxxx

I'm just trying to raise awareness because I am terrified of the fact we have 7-10 years left before we can't save our planet. We have more plastic in the ocean than stars in the galaxy. Please guys x
